# VirtualBox & Oracle Linux 9 Setup

## Step-by-Step

### 1. Download VirtualBox
- Source: virtualbox.org
- Version: 7.x for Windows
- Installed: Yes 

### 2. Download Oracle Linux 9 ISO
- Source: yum.oracle.com/oracle-linux-isos.html
- File: Oracle Linux 9 (x86_64) Full ISO
- Size: ~9 GB
- Downloaded: Yes 

### 3. Create VM in VirtualBox

**Settings:**

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Name | Oracle-Linux-9-Lab |
| Type | Linux |
| Version | Red Hat (64-bit) |
| RAM | 2048 MB |
| CPU | 2 cores |
| Disk | 20 GB |

**Network:** NAT (default)

### 4. Installation Steps
- Language: English
- Software Selection: Minimal Install (for learning)
- Network: Enabled
- Root password: [set but not saved here]
- User created: student

### 5. First Login
- Username: student
- Password: [your password]

